 Voice-Activated AI Chatbot using Streamlit
Overview
This project is a Voice-Enabled AI Chatbot built with Python and Streamlit. It uses speech recognition to listen to voice commands, text-to-speech to respond, and performs real-time tasks like fetching information from Wikipedia, opening websites, managing notes, and greeting the user contextually. The app can be controlled by both voice and text input.
Features
‚Ä¢ Voice Recognition ‚Äî Understands spoken commands via the microphone.
‚Ä¢ Text-to-Speech Response ‚Äî Responds back using realistic voice.
‚Ä¢ Wikipedia Integration ‚Äî Fetches and reads summaries for queries.
‚Ä¢ Smart Greetings ‚Äî Greets the user based on the time of day.
‚Ä¢ Note-Taking ‚Äî Save and display notes interactively.
‚Ä¢ Web Automation ‚Äî Opens websites like YouTube, Google, or GitHub by command.
‚Ä¢ Dual Interaction ‚Äî Accepts both voice and typed commands.
‚Ä¢ Exit Control ‚Äî Stops listening until the user resumes manually.
