Installation
1Ô∏è‚É£ Clone this repository:
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/voice-chatbot.git
cd voice-chatbot
2Ô∏è‚É£ Create a virtual environment (optional but recommended):
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # for Mac/Linux
venv\Scripts\activate      # for Windows
3Ô∏è‚É£ Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt
If you don‚Äôt have a requirements.txt yet, create one with:
streamlit
speechrecognition
pyttsx3
wikipedia
pyaudio
Run the App
Start the chatbot locally using:
streamlit run app.py
The app will open automatically in your browser at http://localhost:8501
How It Works
1. Speech Recognition ‚Äî Listens to your voice using the microphone.
2. Command Processing ‚Äî Interprets and cleans your spoken or typed command.
3. Response Logic ‚Äî Fetches data, opens websites, or saves notes.
4. Text-to-Speech ‚Äî Speaks the response using pyttsx3.
5. Persistent Notes ‚Äî All saved notes are stored in notes.txt and visible in the sidebar.
Example Commands
Command	Action
Hello	Greets back
What is artificial intelligence	Reads a Wikipedia summary
Open YouTube	Opens YouTube in browser
Remember to buy milk	Saves the note
Show notes	Displays saved notes
What‚Äôs the time	Reads the current time
Exit or Stop listening	Pauses the chatbot
